    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single below-required factor (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 1 vs. required Gradation 2) is acknowledged; the assessment team judged that the single-condition F1717 protocol is the regulatory standard and that the strong output-comparison results across all three QoIs (E/uval < 1.96, percentage difference < 2.5%) provide sufficient credibility evidence for a Medium assurance level decision. Model revision completed January 2026 incorporated updated solver settings and refined contact definitions; the primary experimental dataset used for validation dates from the 2018 design-verification campaign and has not been refreshed following the model revision.",
